<DocumentPointerlockerror_event>
<summary>
The <c>pointerlockerror</c> event is fired when locking the pointer failed (for technical reasons or because the permission was denied).
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>This event is not cancelable.</para>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Pointer_Lock_API">Using Pointer Lock API</see><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document/pointerlockerror_event"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
</DocumentPointerlockerror_event>
